<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="314" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d314">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/2522</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                President <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-03">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 3, 1916</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: I enclose a proposed
                                letter<note n="42" xml:id="d314fn1">No copy of this draft found in
                                Department files.</note> in reply to the rejection of our proposal
                            of January 18th, relative to the disarming of merchant vessels.</p>
                        <p>I have already sent you a draft of a letter on this subject,<note n="43" xml:id="d314fn2">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_350">p.
                                350</ref>.</note> and in the enclosed I have sought to meet your
                            views on the previous draft.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>